# Make navigation options clear and consistent across the service

When using a service or website, users should expect a consistent presentation of repeated content such as navigation menus and layout of pages, and an indication of where they are. This is a criteria of <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/consistent-navigation.html" rel="noopner noreferrer" target="_blank">WCAG 3.2.3 - Consistent Navigation (opens in new tab)</a>

This helps screen reader users or magnifier users to quickly and consistently navigate a set of pages as they can expect repeating features to be in the same place or order.

This also assists users to understand where they are in a service and navigate to other areas quickly. This can include styling a navigation option differently to indicate it is the currently selected option. 

Therefore, make sure menus are consistently presented,  <a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/breadcrumbs/" rel="noopner noreferrer" target="_blank">breadcrumbs (opens in new tab)</a> are used in multi-level sites and services and  <a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/back-link/" rel="noopner noreferrer" target="_blank">back links (opens in new tab)</a> are available in transactional services.




